body:
@marcphilipp, In my mind the `TestInstancePostProcessor` and the new class should be named as a common pair of words (like get/set, add/remove, start/stop, ...), because of their logical relation.

But this seems to be not possible due to the naming of the `TestInstancePostProcessor`, or is it possible to rename the existing class? If this would be possible I would prefer to rename `TestInstancePostProcessor` too.

Apart from this i don't have any alternative proposals.
